{"title": "Jobs at WIRED", "text": "WIRED is more than a magazine. It\u2019s more than a website. It\u2019s a family of fiercely creative people driven to tell the most interesting and inspiring stories in the world. That\u2019s a lofty goal, and to achieve it, we need talent. Here\u2019s a list of open positions at WIRED. If you see something interesting, apply!\n\nJobs\n\nAssociate Director of Social Media (NYC)\n\nProducer, Multiplatform (London)\n\n\n\nDirector, Business & Industry (NYC)\n\nAbout WIRED\n\nWIRED is where tomorrow is realized. It is the essential source of information and ideas that make sense of a world in constant transformation. The WIRED conversation illuminates how technology is changing every aspect of our lives\u2014from culture to business, science to design. The breakthroughs and innovations that we uncover lead to new ways of thinking, new connections, and new industries. WIRED reaches more than 30 million people each month through WIRED.com, our digital edition, the magazine, social media, and live events.\n\nAbout Cond\u00e9 Nast\n\nCond\u00e9 Nast is a premier media company renowned for producing the highest-quality content for the world\u2019s most influential audiences. Attracting more than 100 million consumers across its industry-leading print, digital, and video brands, the company\u2019s portfolio includes some of the most iconic titles in media: Vogue, Vanity Fair, Glamour, Brides, Self, GQ, GQ Style, The New Yorker, Cond\u00e9 Nast Traveler, Allure, Architectural Digest, Bon App\u00e9tit, Epicurious, WIRED, W, Golf Digest, Golf World, Teen Vogue, Ars Technica, The Scene, Pitchfork, and Backchannel. The company\u2019s newest division, Cond\u00e9 Nast Entertainment, was launched in 2011 to develop film, television, and premium digital video programming.\n\nFor more information, please visit condenast.com and follow @CondeNast on Twitter.", "authors": "['Cond\u00e9 Nast', 'Andy Greenberg', 'Matt Burgess', 'Caroline Haskins', 'Jessica Rawnsley']", "top_image": "https://www.wired.com/verso/static/wired/assets/favicon.ico", "keywords": "[]", "summary": ""}
