U, India's new rules for AI, Waymo's wins, and Salla's huge pre-IPO round.\n\nWill we reach AGI before Stripe goes public? Welcome to Equity, a podcast about the business of startups, where we unpack the numbers and nuance behind the headlines. Join us as we dig through the most critical stories from the week.\n\nMatch Group\u2019s deal with OpenAI is just business with AI glitter on top The Equity crew is covering deals of the week from PermitFlow, Cake and Match Group, Klarna's board, and which startups could be 2024's winners.\n\nReddit\u2019s upcoming IPO could reward its power users On today's episode, we're talking about Reddit's upcoming IPO (again), along with some impressive raises for edtech startup Loora, Bioptimus and Dili.\n\nThe regulatory clock is ticking for TikTok Crypto prices are up, Planity has raised a hefty Series C, TikTok is in trouble again, and there's a slew of M&A in Startup Land.\n\nLoad More", "authors": "['Theresa Loconsolo', 'The Latest Theresa Loconsolo', 'Apr', 'Mar', 'Feb']", "top_image": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4b4df96a68376605ad2a93573dcd1c74?s=500&d=identicon&r=g", "keywords": "[]", "summary": ""}
